HEADWORD: Emissivity
<hw>Em`is*siv"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Tendency to
emission; comparative facility of emission, or rate at which emission
takes place;</def> <specif>specif.</specif> <fld>(Physics)</fld>,
<def>the rate of emission of heat from a bounding surface per degree of
temperature difference between the surface and surrounding substances
(called by Fourier <altname>external conductivity</altname>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emissory</ent>⟦br⟧
